uccessful practitioner. This book is suitable for ITIL v3 Experts, ITIL 4 MP students, ITSM (IT service management) practitioners who are adopting ITIL 4, approved training organisations, IT service managers, IT managers and those in IT support roles. The guide focuses on: The customer journey; Fostering stakeholder relationships; How to: shape demand and define service offerings, and align expectations and agree service details; Onboarding and offboarding; Continual value co-creation; Realising and validating service value; and Exam preparation. A useful tool throughout your career In addition to being an essential study aid, the author — a seasoned ITSM professional — also provides additional guidance throughout the book, which you can lean on once your training and exam are over. The book includes her own practical experience, from which she gives advice, and points to think about along the way, so that you can refer back to this book for years to come – long after you’ve passed your exam. ITIL® is a registered trade mark of the PeopleCert group. Used under licence from PeopleCert. All rights reserved.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aITIL (Information technology management standard)vStudy guidesxExaminations. 0aITIL (Information technology management standard)vStudy guides. 0aInformation technology projectsvStudy guidesxManagementxExaminations. 0aInformation technologyvStudy guidesxManagementxExaminations. 0aStakeholder management. 0aValue. 7aCOMPUTERS / General.2bisacsh  aClaire Agutter.  aITIL 4 DSV.  aITIL 4 MP DSV.  aITIL 4 book.  aITIL 4 drive stakeholder value.  aITIL 4 managing professional.  aITIL 4 strategic leader.  aITIL 4 study guide.  aITIL 4.  aITIL DSV.  aITIL book.  aITIL drive stakeholder value.  aITIL managing professional.  aITIL qualification.  a